      <!-- ################################################################################################ -->
      <p style = "font-size:24px;color:#0069A8">Ways to Get Involved</p>
        <p><b>Associate Editors:</b> Becoming a member of the editorial board of the journal requires approval of the Conference Editorial Board (CEB).  If you feel you meet these qualifications, feel free to submit a completed copy of our <a href="../files/AE-bio-template.pdf" download="AE-bio-template.pdf" target="_blank">Author Bio form</a> to the OJ-CSYS Editorial Assistant.</p>
        <p><b>Reviewers:</b>  If you are not yet ready to become part of the editorial board, becoming a reviewer is an excellent way to help the journal and gain experience. Reviewers are an integral part of the success of the OJ-CSYS.</p>
	<p> We uphold the highest standards for our peer-reviewed papers, and reviewers help by selecting only the most qualified papers. Reviewers are picked for being leading researchers in the field, likely having authored relevant papers that have been previously presented in high-profile journals and conferences.</p>
	 <p>Reviewers will need to contact the OJ-CSYS editorial assistant after setting themselves up on the <a href="https://css.paperplaza.net/conferences/scripts/pinwizard.pl" template="_blank">Submission Site</a>. Guidelines for reviewers can be found on the<a href="forreviewers.html"> For Reviewers</a> page.</p>
        <p><p><b>Authors</b> are encouraged to submit their papers after setting themselves up on the <a href="https://css.paperplaza.net/conferences/scripts/pinwizard.pl" template="_blank">Submission Site</a>. The Author Guidelines and other helpful tools can be found under <a href="forauthors.html"> For Authors</a>. Please also feel free to reach out to the OJ-CSYS editorial assistant with any questions.</p>
 <br>

      <p style = "font-size:24px;color:#0069A8">The IEEE  Control Systems Society Mission</p>
     <p>Founded in 1954, the Control Systems Society is a world-renowned society dedicated to the advancement of the theory and practice of systems and control which has been at the forefront of the field for over 65 years.</p>
    <p>In keeping with the IEEE’s reputation, publishing with the Open Journal Systems of Control guarantees a rigorous peer-review process and insightful feedback for your research from leading experts in the field. With the priority of quality being of upmost importance, the journal additionally aims at a fast review time of around 6 months from submission to publication on IEEE Xplore.</p>

	
